Soviet Tokarev 9mm Pistol, Model M70A, made by the Zastava Armory in Serbia.
The Tokarev pistol was originally designed and produced by the Russian military during WWII.  It has a 4.5" barrel, windage-adjustable front and rear sights, slide and magazine releases, thumb safety, plastic grips, and two 9-round magazines.  The Tokarev, as well as its variants in 9mm, is renowned for its simplicity, power and accuracy.
This Tokarev M70A comes with the factory plastic fitted carrying case, cleaning brush, instruction manual and proof-house certificate.  The grip panels are a darker forest green, but I'm including another set of grips in black.  I'm also including a correct military holster, with shoulder strap and extra magazine pouch.
